{"hash":"f696d459c27618375ae9beff9077a6039192ee4e","data":{"article":{"id":"ceb6ea2139f017c405a97d3a9ebe044e","title":"Galaxy+Carpentries effort funded by Mozilla Open Science Awards","tease":"Gallantries!","category":"news","date":"2019-03-12","days":null,"contact":"","contact_url":"","fileInfo":{"path":"build/content-md/news/2019-03-galaxy-carpentries/index.md"},"authors":"","location":"","location_url":"","source_blog":"","source_blog_url":"","skip_title_render":null,"redirect":"","autotoc":null,"links":[],"image":"","images":{},"external_url":"","content":"<p><a href=\"https://medium.com/read-write-participate/meet-mozillas-latest-open-science-awardees-cfa45348e5d5#7d0f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><div class=\"img-sizer float-right\" style=\"max-width: 300px\"><img src=\"/images/logos/mozilla-science-lab-logo.png\" alt=\"Mozilla Science Labs funds Galaxy + Carpentries proposal\"></div></a></p>\n<p>At year's <a href=\"http://bh2018paris.info/index.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Biohackathon</a> we (<a href=\"https://github.com/shiltemann\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Saskia</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/bebatut\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Bérénice</a>, and <a href=\"https://github.com/hexylena\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Helena</a> from Galaxy; and <a href=\"https://github.com/mkuzak\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Mateusz Kuzak</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/fpsom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Fotis Psomopoulos</a> from the Carpentries) applied for a <a href=\"https://science.mozilla.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Mozilla Science</a> mini grant based on the idea of creating hybrid training materials (e.g. RNA-seq analysis in Galaxy followed by <a href=\"https://www.carpentries.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Carpentries</a> style R coding for further analysis/visualisation) and piloting those materials in a hybrid workshop (streaming to multiple satellite locations).</p>\n<p>We are pleased to have been <a href=\"https://medium.com/read-write-participate/meet-mozillas-latest-open-science-awardees-cfa45348e5d5#7d0f\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">funded by Mozilla</a> to work on this project.</p>\n<p>The <strong><a href=\"https://galaxy-carpentries.github.io/gallantries/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Gallantries Project</a></strong> will focus on adaptation and delivery of existing training materials from various open communities for High Throughput Sequencing (HTS) data analysis skills needed in genomics research. Collaboration on material adaptation will take place through sprints, and delivery of training will be done at two 3-day workshops.</p>\n<p><strong>Interested? Please join us on <a href=\"https://gitter.im/galaxy-carpentries\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Gitter</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/galaxy-carpentries\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">GitHub</a>.</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/shiltemann\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Saskia</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/bebatut\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Bérénice</a>, <a href=\"https://github.com/hexylena\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Helena</a> ,<a href=\"https://github.com/mkuzak\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Mateusz</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/fpsom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Fotis</a></p>\n"}},"context":{}}